1 charitable donation. "Telephone solicitation" also includes those transactions
2 that are defined as "telemarketing" under the Telemarketing Sales Rule.
3 (10) Telephone solicitor. – Any individual, business establishment, business, or
4 other legal entity person doing business in this State that, directly or through
5 salespersons or agents, makes or makes, attempts to make make, causes to be
6 made, or otherwise provides or knows or consciously avoids knowing that
7 they provide substantial assistance or support for making telephone
8 solicitations or causes telephone solicitations to be made. solicitations.
9 "Telephone solicitor" also includes any party defined as a "telemarketer"
10 under the Telemarketing Sales Rule.
11 (11) Telephone subscriber. – An individual who subscribes to a residential
12 telephone service from a local exchange company, a competing local provider
13 certified to do business in North Carolina, or a wireless telephone company;
14 or the individuals living or residing with that individual.
15 (12) Unsolicited telephone call. – A voice or text communication, whether
16 prerecorded, live, or a facsimile, over a telephone line or wireless telephone
17 network or via a commercial mobile radio service that is made by a person to
18 a telephone subscriber without prior express invitation or permission.
19 "§ 75-102. Restrictions on telephone solicitations.
20 …
21 (f) No telephone solicitor shall make a telephone solicitation before 8:00 A.M. or after
22 9:00 P.M.
23 …
24 (h) No telephone solicitor or robocaller shall engage in threats, intimidation, or the use
25 of profane or obscene language.
26 (i) No telephone solicitor shall cause misleading information to be transmitted to users
27 of caller identification technologies or otherwise block or misrepresent the origin of the telephone
28 solicitation. No provider of telephone caller identification services shall be held liable for
29 violations of this subsection committed by other individuals or entities. It is not a violation of
30 this subsection for a telephone solicitor to utilize the name and number of the entity the
31 solicitation is being made on behalf of rather than the name and number of the telephone solicitor.
32 …
33 (k) Nothing in this section prohibits a telephone solicitor from contacting by
34 nontelephonic notice a telephone subscriber whose telephone number appears in the "Do Not
35 Call" Registry to obtain the telephone subscriber's express invitation or permission prior express
36 written consent allowing the telephone solicitor to make telephone solicitations to the telephone
37 subscriber. A telephone solicitor shall not contact a telephone subscriber by telephone to obtain
38 this express invitation or permission.prior express written consent.
39 (l) Nothing in this section prohibits a telephone solicitor from advertising in a general
40 medium or contacting by nontelephonic notice a telephone subscriber whose telephone number
41 appears in the "Do Not Call" Registry to encourage the telephone subscriber to initiate telephone
42 calls to the telephone solicitor. A telephone solicitor shall not contact a telephone subscriber by
43 telephone to obtain this express invitation or permission.prior express written consent.
